1 AN ACT relating to buildings serving as temporary shelters in times of
2 emergencies.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 ïƒ¢SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 65 IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) If the Governor or the chief executive authority of a city, county, charter county,
7 urban-county government, consolidated local government, or unified local
8 government declares an emergency, the owner of a building may offer temporary
9 shelter to persons, including overnight shelter, if the owner of the building
10 provides written notice to the local government in which it is immediately located
11 in the manner designated by that local government.
12 (2) The city, county, charter county, urban-county government, consolidated local
13 government, or unified local government shall put in place procedures for owners
14 of buildings to notify the local government of their intentions to offer shelter
15 during an emergency.
16 (3) (a) Any local ordinances or state laws that relate to the occupancy or use of the
17 building that may be violated by using the building as a temporary shelter in
18 the manner set out by this section shall be unenforceable during the time an
19 emergency is declared.
20 (b) Once an emergency declaration is no longer in effect, all local or state
21 ordinances or laws relating to the occupancy or use of the building shall be
22 enforceable.
